This paper deals with unsupervised text style transfer, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a dual reinforcement learning framework, which involves training models using reinforcement learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves designing rewards and optimizing models, which are common topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses neural networks, which is a common technique in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves text processing, which is a common topic in cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
